kautoswitch (0.1.0-4) unstable; urgency=low

  * Switch keyboard layout to corrected language after word/phrase correction.
  * Add HANDOFF state: stop all correction after fix, resume on new mismatch.
  * Enforce space/punctuation preservation after correction (boundary char
    always emitted in replacement text).
  * API model selection: fetch available models via /v1/models, dropdown in UI.
  * Selected API model stored in config and sent in correction requests.
  * Polish mode (Ctrl+Shift+L): one-shot cleanup of current line text
    (layout fix + spelling), non-intrusive, deterministic, reversible via Undo.
  * Layout after polish switches to match last word of polished text.
  * New tests: layout switch, space preservation, punctuation, API models,
    polish mode (entire line, selection, layout, no-rewrite), HANDOFF mode.
  * Version bumped to 0.1.0-4.

 -- KAutoSwitch <kautoswitch@localhost>  Sat, 01 Feb 2026 18:00:00 +0000

kautoswitch (0.1.0-2) unstable; urgency=low

  * Fix repeated correction loop after space (word finalization guard).
  * Defer phrase correction to idle timeout (350ms), cancelable on typing.
  * Add input state machine (TYPING, WORD_FINALIZED, IDLE).
  * Phrase correction no longer blocks input.

 -- KAutoSwitch <kautoswitch@localhost>  Sat, 01 Feb 2026 12:00:00 +0000

kautoswitch (0.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Initial release.
  * X11 global keystroke interception via XRecord.
  * Layout correction (QWERTY↔ЙЦУКЕН), typo correction, mixed-layout fix.
  * TinyLLM rule-based engine + optional local API mode.
  * Undo/rethink hotkeys, 3x-undo learning rules.
  * KDE system tray + Qt settings window.
  * systemd user service + XDG autostart.

 -- KAutoSwitch <kautoswitch@localhost>  Sat, 01 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000
